Process:

# source init1
Sets up local ssh agent on the Windows machine

# ./init2
Pulls an ssh certificate that gets the user into Planetlab. Customize with the current user's username and machine where the ssh certificate resides

# ./startP2
Creates a port forwarder from a PlanetLab machine and starts the visualization. The port numbers are as per the three IDF 2006 scenarios.


At this point, p2setup can be called on the controlling machine to start dissemination and startup of P2


# ./shutdown1
Kills the local ssh-agent

